name: Blackberry
description: My morning walk through the mountains brought me to a family of village farmers picking blackberries by hand. They had trimmed and maintained throughout the scorching summer months and now it was time to harvest the tiny puffy fruit. One of the elders held out her hands “They are clean and never felt pesticide” she said proudly. My camera fired at that moment in time and place capturing the fruits of labour in the worn palms of the village farmer. Specs: Digital Photograph, 4816x2710 Jpeg 300 Dpi Photograph and Story by ZORAN Milich
